{"id":39852,"date":"2023-04-21T15:12:04","date_gmt":"2023-04-21T11:12:04","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=39852"},"modified":"2023-04-21T15:12:04","modified_gmt":"2023-04-21T11:12:04","slug":"ayat-of-islam","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/04\/21\/ayat-of-islam\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Deen: What are the signs of Islam?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Mu\u2019awiyah ibn Haydah reported: I said, \u201cO Prophet of Allah, I ask you by the face of Allah Almighty, with what did your Lord send you?\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Islam.<\/strong>\u201d I said, \u201cWhat are the signs of Islam?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>That you declare the surrender of your face to Allah Almighty, relinquish your old ways, perform prayer, and give charity. Every Muslim is sacred to another Muslim, two brothers supporting each other. Allah Almighty will not accept the good deeds of an idolater after he embraces Islam until he leaves the idolaters for the Muslims.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Nasa\u0304&#8217;i\u0304 2568<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em>Hasan<\/em> (fair) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u064f\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0648\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0629 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u062d\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u064e\u0629 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064f\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0646\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u0650\u064a \u0623\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0644\u064f\u0643\u064e \u0628\u0650\u0648\u064e\u062c\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0632\u0651\u064e \u0648\u064e\u062c\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e \u0628\u0650\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0628\u064e\u0639\u064e\u062b\u064e\u0643\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064f\u0643